- "set their sights on reducing their footprint" refers to sectors that have at least one waste reduction target;
- "sectors" are unique areas or divisions within the environmental management system.

- "Environmental burden" refers to the combined impact of waste disposal and greenhouse gas emissions on the environment;
- "CO2 equivalent emissions" (CO2e) are a standardized measure of greenhouse gases, expressing the global warming potential of different gases in terms of CO2;
- "Total environmental impact" encompasses both the physical waste and the greenhouse gas emissions, providing a comprehensive measure of a sector's environmental footprint.

- "Breathing out the most carbon" refers to the sectors with the highest average CO2 equivalent emissions;
- "Slimming down their emissions" refers to the reduction targets set for these sectors;
- CO2 equivalent emissions (CO2e) are a standardized measure that includes the impact of various greenhouse gases, converted to CO2 equivalents for comparison.

- "heaviest burden on the environment" refers to the sector with the highest combined score of total waste disposed, CO2 emissions, and land use area;
- "weight of its waste" refers to the total amount of waste disposed by the sector;
- "cloud of its CO2 emissions" refers to the total CO2 emissions from the sector;
- "extent of its land footprint" refers to the total area of land use by the sector.

- "Heaviest burden of waste disposal" refers to the highest total waste disposed in kilograms;
- "Highest greenhouse gas emissions" refers to the highest total CO2 equivalent emissions;
- "Most ambitious waste reduction targets" refers to the highest average waste reduction targets;
- "Energy consumption levels" are measured in the total energy consumption of the buildings in each sector.

sql:
SELECT sector_id, waste_generated 
FROM commercial_establishments 
WHERE waste_generated > 50;

SELECT establishment_type, waste_generated
FROM commercial_establishments
ORDER BY waste_generated DESC;

